| Feature              | Macro                             | Function                              |
| -------------------- | --------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| Defined by           | `#define`                         | `return_type name(args)`              |
| Evaluated            | Compile-time                      | Runtime                               |
| Type checking        | None                              | Yes                                   |
| Debuggable           | Hard                              | Easy                                  |
| Memory footprint     | None                              | Yes, has instructions in text section |
| Can have body `{ }`? | Rarely, usually single expression | Always                                |


Rule of Thumb

Braces {} and type declaration → function

#define → macro

No runtime memory/code → macro

Callable at runtime → function

Quick “look in code” test

If you see #define → macro

If you see static or int/void/struct → function

Sometimes kernel also has static inline functions → behave like functions but may be inlined at compile-time
